I"^<h3>Remove the Purple-Splash Screen without extension</h3>
<h5><span style="color:purple">Ubuntu ver. 20.04.1 LTS // Gnome Shell ver. 3.36.4 // Date. 2020/08/24 (or 08/24/2020)</span></h5>

<p><strong>우분투 20.04 로그인 직후에 잠깐 나타나던 보라색 화면을 제거해보았습니다.</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>주의!! 저는 프로그래밍 초보입니다. 이 방법으로 문제가 생길 가능성은 많습니다.</li>
  <li>따라하시기 전에 한번 더 심사숙고 하시고 문제가 없는지 검색해보셔야만 합니다.</li>
  <li><span style="color:red"> <strong>요약</strong></span>: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libgnome-shell.so</code> 파일을 찾아 <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">#4f194c</code> 색 코드를 변경하시면 됩니다.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>I just found the way to remove purple-splash screen after login-inin Ubuntu.</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>WARNING!! I am very very newbie, so my solution may be wrong.</li>
  <li>Before trying this, I recommend you to find another solution. Maybe there is some better one!</li>
  <li><span style="color:red"> <strong>Summary</strong></span>: Find the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libgnome-shell.so</code> file, and change the color code <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">#4f194c</code>.</li>
</ul>

<h2>방법</h2>
<ol>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libgnome-shell.so</code>파일을 찾습니다. 제 경우에는 <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/usr/lib/gnome-shell/</code>에 있었습니다.</li>
  <li>만약 찾기 어려우시다면, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">find</code>기능을 사용하여 <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">#4f194c</code> 색 코드를 갖고 있는 문서를 찾아보세요.</li>
  <li>코드 예시: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo find /usr/ -type f -print 2&gt; /dev/null | xargs grep -i "#4f194c" 2&gt;/dev/null</code></li>
  <li>파일을 여신 후에 약 <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">39116</code>번째 줄에 있는 <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">#4f194c</code> 색 코드를 변경해주세요. 저는 검은색(<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">#000000</code>)으로 하였습니다.</li>
  <li>이후 재부팅을 하시면 로그인 직후에 잠깐 나타나던 보라색 화면이 나오지 않는 걸 확인하실 수 있습니다!</li>
</ol>

<h2>Solution</h2>
<ol>
  <li>find your <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libgnome-shell.so</code> file. In my case, That is in <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/usr/lib/gnome-shell/</code></li>
  <li>If you cannot find the file, you can use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">find</code>. Find the color code <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">#4f194c</code>.</li>
  <li>Eg. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo find /usr/ -type f -print 2&gt; /dev/null | xargs grep -i "#4f194c" 2&gt;/dev/null</code></li>
  <li>And just modify the color code in about <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">39116</code>th row. In my case, I set the color code <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">#000000</code>(black).</li>
  <li>And DONE!! There will be no-purple-screen in your loging situation!</li>
</ol>

